scroll-container heuristic, anchor threshold, or pre-erase rules for known-bad
sites (chatgpt.com, claude.ai, x.com) costs little and fixes a lot. You
already have site-specific behavior implicit in the codebase — making it      
explicit is cheaper than chasing universal correctness.

