- "Remove things like this" (#11, the "killer feature") — This is the most interesting idea in the whole list. After erasing one element, find structurally similar siblings and offer bulk removal. This plays to FuzzyAnchor's strengths — you could score all siblings of the erased element's parent against the erased element's anchor and surface high-confidence matches. Worth prototyping.

